ted by the Normans and introduced by them to England, displacing the Old English form <i>Æþelbeorht</i>. The name is popular in a variety of forms in Western Europe, and has been traditional in a number of European princely families. It was out of favour in England for centuries, however, and the revival of its popularity in the 19th century was largely in honour of  Queen Victoria's  consort,  Prince Albert of Saxe-Coburg-Gotha ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Gwyn ap Cloddien was born in 1015 as the son of Clodien Ap Gwrdri Hir. He had at least 2 sons."},"et":{"1015–":"1015–Surnud","1015–Male":"1015–Surnud","1045–Male":"1045–Surnud","0894–Male":"0894–Surnud","1015":"1015","0894":"0894","1045":"1045"},"fi":{"1015–":"1015–Kuollut","1015–Male":"1015–Kuollut","1045–Male":"1045–Kuollut","0894–Male":"0894–Kuollut","1015":"1015","0894":"0894","1045":"1045"},"fr":{"1015–":"1015–Décédé","1015–Male":"1015–Décédé","1045–Male":"1045–Décédé","0894–Male":"0894–Décédé","1015":"1015","0894":"0894","1045":"1045","lifeSummary":"Gwyn ap Cloddien est né en 1015, fils de Clodien Ap Gwrdri Hir. Il a eu au moins 2 fils."},"de":{"1015–":"1015–Verstorben","1015–Male":"1015–Verstorben","1045–Male":"1045–Verstorben","0894–Male":"0894–Verstorben","1015":"1015","0894":"0894","1045":"1045","lifeSummary":"Gwyn ap Cloddien wurde 1015, als Sohn von Clodien Ap Gwrdri Hir geboren. Er hatte mindestens 2 Söhne."},"ht":{"1015–":"1015–Desede","1015–Male":"1015–Desede","1045–Male":"1045–Desede","0894–Male":"0894–Desede","1015":"1015","0894":"0894","1045":"1045"},"hu":{"1015–":"1015–elhunyt","1015–Male":"1015–elhunyt","1045–Male":"1045–elhunyt","0894–Male":"0894–elhunyt","1015":"1015","0894":"0894","1045":"1045"},"id":{"1015–":"1015–Telah Meninggal","1015–Male":"1015–TelahMeninggal","1045–Male":"1045–TelahMeninggal","0894–Male":"0894–Telah Meninggal","1015":"1015","0894":"0894","1045":"1045"},"it":{"1015–":"1015–Deceduto","1015–Male":"1015–Deceduto","1045–Male":"1045–Deceduto","0894–Male":"0894–Deceduto","1015":"1